title: For Sale/Trade:  Sterling .25, well made american classic, NOT saturday night special or junk gun
postcontent:
For those of you who think you can identify "junk guns", "chuck'n'run guns", or "saturday night specials", by looks, here is a little background.  Those guns known to be very cheap in price and for poor quality and poor reliability were generally made by one of 6 California based companies (often known as the ring of fire) here in the US, or were cheap imports from before the FFA of 1968 was enforced.  These guns were made of what is commonly referred to as "pot metal", such as zinc castings, alloys with melting points below 800 degrees Fahrenheit, powder metallurgy, or other low-cost manufacturing techniques. The only steel parts were often linings or inserts in the barrel and chamber.  These guns were known to crack, break, bend, and even explode after firing so many rounds. The US companies are Bryco Arms, Jimenez Arms, Jennings Firearms, Raven Arms, Lorcin Engineering, and Davis Industries (now Cobra Arms).

Sterling is a New York based company that started in 1968. They began manufacturing the E&R designed compact handguns in 1972 and produced them up until about 1986. The company moved from Buffalo, to Gasport, to Lockport, but stayed in NY throughout its life.  These handguns were machined from steel and steel only.  There are no cheap metals in these designs at all. These designs were manufactured through traditional machining. Their weight is a testament to that, and the fact that there are still so many of them in existence, and reliable use, is also a sign of their quality.

This particular gun was purchased by my great uncle in the mid 70's for use as a pocket gun while working on his farm in South Dakota, it was then handed down to my grandmother for a purse gun, and then to my mother who has used it as her purse gun. I have now been carrying it as a pocket gun for the last few months.  I have personally put approximately 200 rounds through it.  It is rock solid reliable. 

It comes with 2 magazines that hold 6 rounds each.  One magazine is the original that came with it, and with this magazine there has NEVER been a single FTE or FTF.  The second magazine we bought at a gun show and it does have some issues.  The rear of the cartridges tend to hang up when feeding out of this magazine sometimes, and will stovepipe the live round. It is easy to clear it when this happens, but its a definite concern.  It will either need to have some work done to the top edges, or just be replaced.  I have it marked so that I only ever use it as a "back up" magazine. 

Its a great little gun. I am selling it simply because I've decided I want to switch to a .22 caliber pocket gun, because all my others are .22, and I'd like to only buy one kind of ammo for everything.  I will consider trades for .22 semiauto pistols.

I also have .25 ACP ammo. 100 rounds of FMJ target ammo, and 25 rounds of Hornady XTP (JHP), that I will sell for another $40.

Willing to ship to some states. Transfer must be handled through FFL, even for local sale or trade.

Browning - Safari BAR II, 30-06 Sprg, Semi-Auto with BOSS, 20" barrel - 23" with BOSS, Made in Belgium, near new condition, Center Point 4-16x40mm red green illuminated scope * Mil-dot reticle * 10 yds to infinity parallax adjustment * flip open lens caps * fully coated lenses * nitrogen-filled * shockproof * fogproof * waterproof *  (107NV28xxx) Additional pictures available. 
I would take another $75 off if you take just the rifle.
Browning's Ballistic Optimizing Shooting System (BOSS) is a patented breakthrough in rifle accuracy. When any rifle is fired, the barrel goes through a series of vibrations as the bullet leaves the muzzle. The variations of these vibrations greatly affect the accuracy of the rifle. Controlling these vibrations will greatly control the accuracy of the rifle. Browning's BOSS allows you to control the vibrations of your barrel so you can shoot groups you didn't think possible.

How the BOSS works.
 The BOSS simply tunes the vibrations of your barrel. This allows the bullet to leave the barrel the split second it is stationary. The BOSS manual has a list of settings for each caliber and bullet weight. Adjusting your BOSS to these "Sweet Spot" settings allows you to find the instant your barrel is stationary. The result is accuracy never achieved before by an out-of-the-box rifle.
Will ship to your FFL

Made by ACHA-Domingo this is a "Looking Glass" .32acp caliber pistol.
These guns were produced in Spain in the 1920's-1930's and carried by some officers in WWII.
Its a pocket sized semiauto.
Has a sweet safty that doubles as a slide lock.

But if your just looking for something interesting to take to the range that's unique and got a cool history this is also for you!

title: For Sale/Trade:  Mint Condition Lee Enfield Ishapore Rifle 308 win. Very Accurate
postcontent:
I have here a excellent condition Ishapore Lee enfield in 308. These rifles were made for the Indian Military back in the 1960's.  They are very rare, especially one this nice. Ive seen these in worse condition go for $500 at gun shows and on gun auction sites.
This rifle is in pretty good condition for a 60 year old milsurp rifle. The stock has some bangs and notches in it, but its still very sturdy. the original stock was broken when i got it, so i did put a new stock on it that is very nice condition. 

**When i got it, it was quite dirty, so i dissembled it, cleaned it all out, and have kept it that way ever since. The internals are all very clean and sturdy. It is not a piece of junk, dirty/rusty milsurp rifle. Would make a very nice deer or elk rifle.

**This gun is an amazing shooter for such an old rifle. I dont think it was shot more than 50 times, the bore looks very new. At 100 yards with irons, my bad eyes, on a elbow rest i got a 4 inch group from standard 308 fmj. I sure this gun could pull at least 2 inch groups if not better at 100 yards with a scope or handloads.

There are scope mounts made for it, as seen here. Its a non permanent modification too! I just havent gotten into it yet, but i was planing on scoping it with this mount here. 
http://www.gunaccessories.com/scopes/mounts/lee-enfield-scope-mount-1-mk-iii.html


Looking for a few things to trade for, will add cash or extras such as ammo, scopes, if you have what im really looking for.\

Read more about the gun here if youre interested

title: For Sale/Trade:  FNH USA FNS-9 - Night Sights, 2-tone, holsters
postcontent:
The short story:

I'm selling my FNH FNS-9. This is a 9mm polymer striker-fired handgun with a 4" barrel. The body is black and the slide is stainless steel. Comes with 3 17-round magazines, a smaller back-strap, a chamber lock, a hard case, a SigTac Level 2 Retention holster with a paddle attachment, and a SigTac double mag holster for the extra mags. 

The long story:

This gun is a well thought out design, and has many cool features:

- 3-dot combat night sights with a deep rear sight notch for great accuracy.
- Low bore axis. Recoil centers better on the hand, making for less perceived recoil and much faster and more accurate follow-up shots.
- 5 safeties: Manual, Trigger, Firing Pin, Drop, and Out-Of-Battery safeties
- Accessory rail
- Changeable back-straps for a perfect fit in your hand
- Ambidextrous safety, slide lock, and magazine release
- Beveled slide and frame for easy holstering
- Loaded chamber indicator

Comes with 3 17-round magazines, a smaller back-strap, a chamber lock, a hard case, a SigTac Level 2 Retention holster with a paddle attachment, and a SigTac double mag holster for the extra mags. Level 2 retention means that it has 2 levels of retention: Friction and a button lock. The holster allows for a full master grip, and the button is pressed naturally by your index finger on the draw.

This has about 600 rounds through it. I've never had a failure to fire or any other problem. Makes for a great reliable all-around gun for personal defense, a duty weapon, or just fun at the range. The low bore axis makes the recoil very manageable. Great for the wife if she doesn't like snappy recoil! I trust my life to this weapon, and you will too.

Give me a call or text at 5 5 Nine 3 Five 5 8 0 Six One.
